race.comment: ASTRO WORLD (3) missed narrowly two back before getting too far back at Pinjarra in the Grandstand Cup last time out as favourite. Out to the mile now looks a good move and while he's likely to get back from the draw, he rates highly on recent efforts. Still has upside and can bounce back to winning ways. SOLDANELLE (1) tried her hand in the Jungle Dawn last start but was just outclassed. Her prior form stacks up in a race like this and she now gets Pike in the saddle from a good gate. Everything points to a forward showing back in grade. KELORA (2) has been knocking on the door for a while now and wasn't far away in the Grandstand Cup last time out. Should be in a handy spot from the draw and is expected to be in the finish once again. IDEALLY (8) gets the blinkers on now back in grade and finally draws a good gate. Can improve sharply. EXTREME LOVE (6) missed in a photo last start behind a progressive type and can feature back in trip.
